\section{Solver prerequisite}{

Solver-backed grading uses Gurobi by default. Open backends are explicit:
HiGHS uses the \code{highs} package directly, while GLPK and SYMPHONY route
through ROI plugins. The package installs, loads, and most structural tests
run without a Gurobi license.
}

\section{Status}{

This is a pre-release development build. The bundled M1 gate records
\code{ACCEPTED} for the scoped one-level race/gender surface. The bundled M2 gate
records \code{PARTIAL_ACCEPTED}: L01 industry grade counts pass exactly, gender L02
continuous rows are promoted to \code{banded} by fixture parity, race L02
continuous rows remain \code{approximate} because the \code{Pi_theta} fixture gap is
above the 0.01 promotion boundary, and N10 support rows are synthetic guard
evidence rather than registered paper-value passes. The M2 simulation
fallback is retained as approximate evidence; deterministic quadrature is the
primary M2 path.
}

\section{Getting started}{

Read \code{vignette("a1-getting-started", package = "gradepath")} for a one-call
walkthrough, then reach for \code{\link[=krw_report_card]{krw_report_card()}}. The applied vignettes
(\code{a1}--\code{a5}) cover the workflow, reading and exporting results, the figure
cookbook, and the solvers; the methodological vignettes (\code{m1}--\code{m5}) carry the
estimand-by-estimand derivations and the calibration scope.
}

